
Build the container image with

	docker build -t custodia .

On IPA-enrolled machine, follow the keytab and privileged steps
from https://pypi.python.org/pypi/custodia.ipa.

Then run the container with

	mkdir /var/run/custodia
	docker run --rm -ti \
		-v /etc/ipa:/etc/ipa:ro \
		-v /etc/krb5.conf:/etc/krb5.conf:ro \
		-v /etc/krb5.conf.d:/etc/krb5.conf.d:ro \
		-v /var/lib/sss/pubconf/krb5.include.d:/var/lib/sss/pubconf/krb5.include.d:ro \
		-v /etc/custodia/custodia.keytab:/etc/custodia/custodia.keytab:ro \
		-v /var/run/custodia:/var/run/custodia \
		custodia

